Males can be distinguished from all other members of the genus by the combination of the following characters: profemora black, meso- and metapleura with distinct triangular black marking and shape of the semitergites (
Fig. 8K, M–N
); females: tergites II–VII with a posteromedian granule and praeopercular organ of female wide and not strongly tapered (
Fig. 8C
).
